<https://registry.inspire.gv.at/codelist/vbgLandUseValue/FF> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> "Zones shall be determined as areas to be kept clear that, in the public interest, especially for the protection of the landscape and the site of local character or due to the natural conditions (groundwater level, soil condition, risk of avalanches, of flooding, of landslide, of rockfall and of slide etc.) have to be kept free of building. All open spaces, that are not zoned as agricultural or exceptional areas, are areas to be kept clear. On forest areas, the construction of buildings and facilities is permitted, as far as it is necessary for silvicultural purposes."@en <https://registry.inspire.gv.at/codelist/vbgLandUseValue:1> .
